    "abstractNote": "In previous studies I have drawn attention to the place of martyrs in the preaching and thought of Severus of Antioch. Indeed, there is a preponderance of homilies on martyrs. In the present chapter Severus\u2019 treatment of Stephen, Thallelaius, Sergius and Bacchus, and the trio Tarachus, Probus, and Andronicus will be examined. A concomitant consideration will be the extent to which these homilies evince Severus\u2019 use of martyrial <i>passiones </i>and <i>acta</i>.",
